Breeding male.description: Breeding male Lark Buntings have large white patches on the wing but not on the back or rump like breeding male Bobolinks.

Nonbreeding male.description: Nonbreeding male Lark Buntings have dark streaking down the belly and are darker overall than female/nonbreeding Bobolinks, which have unstreaked bellies. Also note white wing patch on Buntings, but not on female/nonbreeding Bobolinks.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Lark Buntings have streaked bellies while female/nonbreeding Bobolinks have streaked backs. They also have thicker bills than Bobolinks.

Breeding male (Red-winged).description: Breeding male Red-winged Blackbirds are entirely black except for the red and yellow shoulder patches unlike male Bobolinks, which are black and white overall.

Female (Red-winged).description: Female Red-winged Blackbirds are darker overall and more heavily streaked throughout than female/nonbreeding Bobolinks.

Adult.description: Grasshopper Sparrows have more complicated head patterns, with streaks on the back of the neck instead of the Bobolink’s smooth, buffy head.
